Package uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.operation.impl.compare

Class Max

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.operation.impl.compare.Max
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, ElementComparison, Input<Iterable<? extends Element>>, InputOutput<Iterable<? extends Element>,​Element>, MultiInput<Element>, Output<Element>, Operation
    public class Max
extends Object
implements InputOutput<Iterable<? extends Element>,​Element>, MultiInput<Element>, ElementComparison
    A Max operation is intended as a terminal operation for retrieving the "maximum" element from an Iterable of Elements. /** The Elements are compared using the provided Comparators. Either implement your own comparators or use the ElementPropertyComparator.

    The provided element comparators will be use sequentially to compare the operation input iterable to find the maximum.

    See Also:
    Max.Builder, ElementPropertyComparator
